1251
01:38:54,800 --> 01:38:58,700
Americans spend $ 1 25 billion
a year on health.

1252
01:38:58,900 --> 01:39:00,200
More than defense.

1253
01:39:00,800 --> 01:39:03,600
Because Americans believe
in medical care.

1254
01:39:03,800 --> 01:39:08,500
These great hospital complexes
are the cathedrals of our age.

1255
01:39:08,700 --> 01:39:12,200
Billions of dollars,
thousands of beds...

1256
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:17,000
...a whole nation of sick people
turning to us for help.

1257
01:39:23,900 --> 01:39:25,900
You ought to see somebody.

1258
01:39:26,100 --> 01:39:28,300
They're children, Sue.

1259
01:39:28,800 --> 01:39:30,300
They trust us.

1260
01:39:31,800 --> 01:39:33,800
We can't tell them everything.

1261
01:39:34,700 --> 01:39:39,300
Our job is to make things easier
for them. l'm sure you agree.

1262
01:39:40,600 --> 01:39:42,100
You're killing people.

1263
01:39:42,700 --> 01:39:46,100
We must always take the long view...

1264
01:39:46,700 --> 01:39:50,800
...not of the individual,
but of society as a whole...

1265
01:39:51,000 --> 01:39:55,300
...because medicine is now
a great social force.

1266
01:39:56,000 --> 01:39:59,100
The individual is too small.

1267
01:40:08,600 --> 01:40:10,100
That's the drug.

1268
01:40:10,700 --> 01:40:15,000
lt produces abdominal spasm
and peritoneal symptoms.

1269
01:40:16,000 --> 01:40:17,700
lt must be very painful.

1270
01:40:20,100 --> 01:40:21,400
lt's too bad.

1271
01:40:23,200 --> 01:40:26,200
But look at it from
the practical standpoint.

1272
01:40:26,500 --> 01:40:30,900
Somebody has to make these decisions.
We can't wait around forever.

1273
01:40:31,300 --> 01:40:33,500
lf society won't decide,
we'll decide.

1274
01:40:33,700 --> 01:40:35,500
We'll make the hard decisions.

1275
01:40:43,100 --> 01:40:44,700
This is Dr. Harris.

1276
01:40:44,900 --> 01:40:48,800
Schedule an emergency
appendectomy in O.R. 8.

1277
01:40:49,500 --> 01:40:51,600
lt's a member of the house staff,
Dr. Wheeler.

1278
01:40:51,800 --> 01:40:54,500
l've examined her.
She requires immediate surgery.

1279
01:40:54,700 --> 01:40:56,200
Okay, honey, now just sit up.

1280
01:40:56,400 --> 01:40:58,900
Come on, that's it.
That's good.

1281
01:41:01,200 --> 01:41:02,400
Here we go.

1282
01:41:03,300 --> 01:41:04,400
lt's...

1283
01:41:04,700 --> 01:41:05,700
...the drug.

1284
01:41:08,100 --> 01:41:09,700
Doctors make the worst patients.

1285
01:41:09,900 --> 01:41:11,900
They know too much, l guess.

1286
01:41:26,400 --> 01:41:28,100
Why'd you run away?

1287
01:41:28,600 --> 01:41:31,900
l was just talking to your mother.
She was worried about you.

1288
01:41:32,100 --> 01:41:34,300
Everybody's been worried about you.

1289
01:41:38,800 --> 01:41:40,400
Honey, l love you.

1290
01:41:41,300 --> 01:41:42,700
You're gonna be just fine.

1291
01:41:43,000 --> 01:41:44,700
No, Mark, listen.

1292
01:41:45,000 --> 01:41:46,800
You have to stop this.

1293
01:41:47,000 --> 01:41:49,600
l'm fine. l am.

1294
01:41:50,900 --> 01:41:53,100
But your appendix is not fine.

1295
01:41:53,400 --> 01:41:56,700
You've got plus-four peritonitis,
guarding and spasm, honey.

1296
01:41:56,900 --> 01:41:58,700
Susan, you do.

1297
01:41:59,000 --> 01:42:00,400
No, l don't.

1298
01:42:02,400 --> 01:42:04,200
There's no question about it.

1299
01:42:07,800 --> 01:42:11,400
Check my white count
and sed. rate. lt's normal.

1300
01:42:12,100 --> 01:42:13,600
Please.

1301
01:42:21,800 --> 01:42:23,700
The tests aren't here.

1302
01:42:25,400 --> 01:42:28,900
But with these physical signs,
it has to be appendicitis.

1303
01:42:29,100 --> 01:42:29,900
Please!

1304
01:42:30,100 --> 01:42:32,500
lt's better to be safe
and have the operation.

1305
01:42:33,100 --> 01:42:34,800
Besides, you're in the best of hands.

1306
01:42:35,000 --> 01:42:38,400
Dr. Harris himself will do
the procedure. How about that?

1307
01:42:38,700 --> 01:42:40,600
The chief of surgery
is taking your case.

1308
01:42:40,800 --> 01:42:42,000
l don't want him.

1309
01:42:42,200 --> 01:42:45,800
-Well, how's our patient doing?
-Fine. Just slightly delirious.

1310
01:42:46,000 --> 01:42:48,600
That's normal with appendicitis.

1311
01:42:48,900 --> 01:42:51,800
Besides, we all know doctors
make the worst patients.

1312
01:42:52,100 --> 01:42:53,300
You gonna scrub in?

1313
01:42:53,500 --> 01:42:56,900
Dr. Harris, we have O.R. 7
ready for your case.

1314
01:42:57,100 --> 01:42:58,900
l wanted O.R. 8.

1315
01:42:59,100 --> 01:43:00,700
lt isn't ready yet.

1316
01:43:00,900 --> 01:43:05,400
-l specifically requested O.R. 8.
-lt'll take a couple of minutes.

1317
01:43:05,600 --> 01:43:09,300
Well, hurry it up. Our patient
can't wait all night, can she?

1318
01:43:10,800 --> 01:43:11,800
You scrubbing in?

1319
01:43:12,700 --> 01:43:15,600
Excuse me.
Let me just answer this page, sir.

1320
01:43:21,600 --> 01:43:23,200
Yeah, this is Dr. Bellows.

1321
01:43:23,400 --> 01:43:24,400
<i>Yes, Dr. Bellows.</i>

1322
01:43:24,700 --> 01:43:25,700
lt's that serious?

1323
01:43:26,100 --> 01:43:28,000
<i>Is what that serious?</i>

1324
01:43:28,200 --> 01:43:29,700
l'll be right there.

1325
01:43:29,900 --> 01:43:31,500
<i>Dr. Bellows?</i>

1326
01:43:34,300 --> 01:43:36,100
We're ready in O.R. 8.

1327
01:43:36,300 --> 01:43:37,800
We'll start at once.

1328
01:43:38,000 --> 01:43:39,100
Bellows?

1329
01:43:39,400 --> 01:43:41,500
Patient on surgical two's
got convulsions.

1330
01:43:41,700 --> 01:43:43,700
Join me as soon as you can.

1331
01:43:44,000 --> 01:43:45,700
You can take her in.

1332
01:43:46,400 --> 01:43:50,200
You certainly are lucky
with Dr. Harris doing the operation.

1333
01:43:50,500 --> 01:43:52,900
Couldn't ask for a better man, huh?

1334
01:43:53,100 --> 01:43:54,800
-l want--
-Now, now, just lie there.

1335
01:43:55,100 --> 01:43:57,900
You're going to have a nice sleep.
Just relax.

1336
01:43:58,300 --> 01:44:00,100
Easy, we'll take good care of you.

1337
01:44:01,100 --> 01:44:04,400
<i>I found the oxygen line.</i>
<i>It starts in the basement...</i>

1338
01:44:04,600 --> 01:44:06,500
<i>...and it goes up the main tunnel...</i>

1339
01:44:06,700 --> 01:44:10,200
<i>...and then it plugs in the ceiling</i>
<i>that goes to O.R. 8.</i>

1340
01:44:15,200 --> 01:44:16,800
Do we have enough sponges?

1341
01:44:17,000 --> 01:44:20,700
We better order some more
4-0 Chromex. We're almost out.

1342
01:44:41,600 --> 01:44:43,900
We have to do this one right.

1343
01:44:44,500 --> 01:44:49,400
House officers deserve the very best
of care in their own hospital.

1344
01:44:54,400 --> 01:44:58,000
l'm giving you Pentothal.
Take some good, deep breaths, dear.

1345
01:45:00,100 --> 01:45:01,500
ln and out.

1346
01:45:22,800 --> 01:45:24,300
The patient's film.

1347
01:45:25,100 --> 01:45:26,700
They look normal, don't they?

1348
01:45:27,000 --> 01:45:31,300
Pity acute appendicitis doesn't
show up more clearly in the x-rays.

1349
01:45:39,000 --> 01:45:40,400
She has an inny.

1350
01:45:40,600 --> 01:45:41,800
A what?

1351
01:45:42,000 --> 01:45:44,500
An inny. The bellybutton.

1352
01:45:44,800 --> 01:45:47,400
Some are innies, some are outties.
Hers is an inny.

1353
01:46:05,800 --> 01:46:08,200
Let me know when she's fully under.

1354
01:46:13,500 --> 01:46:15,300
She's ready for you.

1355
01:46:16,100 --> 01:46:16,900
Scalpel, please.

1356
01:47:03,900 --> 01:47:04,800
What's that?

1357
01:47:05,000 --> 01:47:06,600
lt's a PVC.

1358
01:47:08,300 --> 01:47:09,300
There's another one.

1359
01:47:09,900 --> 01:47:11,100
Too light?

1360
01:47:11,500 --> 01:47:12,700
l don't think so, sir.

1361
01:47:13,500 --> 01:47:15,200
Maybe you'd better deepen anesthesia.

1362
01:47:26,000 --> 01:47:28,500
Blood pressure's dropping.
l don't understand.

1363
01:47:29,400 --> 01:47:31,000
Want me to stop?

1364
01:47:32,800 --> 01:47:33,800
lt'll be all right.

1365
01:47:34,400 --> 01:47:38,500
-l'll be happy to stop a moment.
-lt's okay, Dr. Harris.

1366
01:47:38,900 --> 01:47:40,200
You recommend l go on?

1367
01:47:56,400 --> 01:47:59,100
Son of a bitch! Son of a bitch!

1368
01:48:01,200 --> 01:48:02,600
Here it is.

1369
01:48:05,600 --> 01:48:08,000
Looks normal.
Never know it from her symptoms.

1370
01:48:08,300 --> 01:48:11,200
lt's nice to see the chief
get caught sometimes.

1371
01:48:12,000 --> 01:48:13,500
Happens to the best of us.

1372
01:48:30,400 --> 01:48:31,400
All right.

1373
01:48:33,100 --> 01:48:35,000
-You can bring her out now.
-Right.

1374
01:48:44,600 --> 01:48:46,600
She's not coming around.

1375
01:48:46,900 --> 01:48:50,000
Just give her a minute.
l'm sure she'll be fine.

1376
01:48:50,200 --> 01:48:51,200
l don't know.

1377
01:49:02,800 --> 01:49:04,300
She's okay, sir.

1378
01:49:04,900 --> 01:49:07,000
She's just fine, Dr. Harris.

1379
01:49:07,400 --> 01:49:08,900
Nice case, Dr. Harris.

1380
01:49:53,900 --> 01:49:56,600
-Don't let him do the operation.
-l know, baby.

